  "summary": "Main\nBy Armen Azizian\nAs of 22nd July, Europe's seaborne crude/condensate imports in July (days 1-31) are observed at 10.5mbd, the lowest level since October 2021. It represents a 100kbd m-o-m decline and 1mbd y-o-y decline. This decline in crude import demand comes at a time where imports would be expected to be higher in the year, given its the summer season (peak demand).",
